&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For Informal Enquiries Contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Angela Kirkby, Clinical Lead Physiotherapist - email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;angelakirkby@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, Tel – 07980729768&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CountyDurham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust is one of the largest integrated care providers in England, serving a population of around 600,000 people. We are a high performing organisation with a track record of success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to join our established Community Therapy Team. The successful applicant will work within this integrated team which is based at Bishop Auckland Hospital, covering Sedgefield Borough and Durham-Dales areas. This will involve the physiotherapy assessment of patients / planning of and contributing to their on-going rehabilitation and timely discharge. As part of our team you will contribute to the wider service providing input into Intermediate Care beds and community crisis service in addition to community visits. You will be expected to have both a high standard of clinical knowledge and demonstrate excellent team working abilities within the multidisciplinary team. Lone working and an ability to travel across the area covered is expected for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have support and supervision from senior Physiotherapy staff and regular supervision / case review meetings. Your development will be supported by MDT leads working within these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
